      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the contingency part. but with the escrow agent \"guarding\" the money like a referee, it feels like they are just sitting on a big pile of cash that isn't theirs. does that ever cause issues? like, what if there's a dispute over who actually \"owns\" that money in the middle of the mess? it sounds like they're basically just holding onto a hoard of assets until everyone stops fighting.",
